Template: debian-installer/zinstaller-remote/title
Type: text
_Description: Choose Zentyal edition to install

Template: zinstaller-remote/user
Type: string
_Description: E-mail address:
 If you have a Zentyal account, you can enter your e-mail address now.
 If not, you can continue the installation leaving this blank.

Template: zinstaller-remote/pass
Type: password
_Description: Password:
 Please enter the password for your Zentyal account.

Template: zinstaller-remote/auth_failed
Type: boolean
_Description: Authentication failed
 The provided account is not valid. Do you want to try to enter your
 credentials again? If not, Zentyal Community edition will be installed.

Template: zinstaller-remote/auth_ok_community
Type: note
_Description: Congratulations!
 Your account has been validated. Zentyal Community edition is going to be
 installed and your server will be automatically registered.

Template: zinstaller-remote/no_register
Type: note
_Description: Continue installation
 As your provided credentials were not valid, Zentyal Community edition will be
 installed.

Template: zinstaller-remote/select_bundle
Type: select
Choices: ${CHOICES}
_Description: Choose the server to install:

Template: zinstaller-remote/select_hostname_recover
Type: select
Choices: ${CHOICES}
_Description: Choose the server to recover:

Template: zinstaller-remote/auth_ok_profesional
Type: note
_Description: Congratulations!
 Your account has been validated. Zentyal Professional edition is going
 to be installed.

Template: zinstaller-remote/auth_ok_business
Type: note
_Description: Congratulations!
 Your account has been validated. Zentyal Business edition is going to be
 installed.

Template: zinstaller-remote/auth_ok_premium
Type: note
_Description: Congratulations!
 Your account has been validated. Zentyal Premium edition is going to be
 installed.

Template: zinstaller-remote/no_bundles
Type: note
_Description: Error
 Currently there are no available editions for your account.
 Installation of Community edition will continue.

Template: zinstaller-remote/error_register
Type: note
_Description: Error
 A problem ocurred while trying to register your server. Please contact support.
 Community edition will be installed if you want to continue:
 "${ERROR}"

Template: zinstaller-remote/error_dr
Type: note
_Description: Disaster Recovery
 You can not recover from a disater without a valid Small Business or
 Enterprise edition. Installation of Community edition will continue.

Template: zinstaller-remote/error_backups
Type: note
_Description: No backups available
 You cannot recover from a disaster if there are no configuration backups
 associated with your account. Regular installation will continue.
